        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Module Learning Objectives\n",
        "\n",
        "By the end of Module 2, students should be able to:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. move from cleaned text to structured representations\n",
        "2. compare sparse and dense text representations\n",
        "3. interpret semantic similarity in a business-text setting\n",
        "4. save representation artifacts for later assignments\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tutorial Learning Objectives\n",
        "\n",
        "By the end of this tutorial, you will:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Load a small set of SEC chunks.\n",
        "2. Build or load dense embeddings.\n",
        "3. Compare cosine neighbors for a few finance-related terms or passages.\n",
        "4. Interpret what semantic proximity captures that TF-IDF does not.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Recommended Dataset\n",
        "\n",
        "Use one of the following:\n",
        "\n",
        "- `assignment01/chunks.csv` from the SEC 10-K workflow\n",
        "- a small local sample of Item 1A or Item 7 chunks\n",
        "- a small text subset built from `data/SEC-10K-2024`\n",
        "\n",
        "## How This Tutorial Connects\n",
        "\n",
        "- `M02_Lab1` and `M02_Lab2` prepare the text artifacts used here.\n",
        "- `M02_A` asks students to reason about whether learned representations improve over count-based features.\n",
        "- Later retrieval and RAG modules depend on students understanding semantic neighborhoods early.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Setup"
      ],
      "id": "5837b227"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
        "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer"
      ],
      "id": "14e592b1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 1: Load Chunked SEC Text"
      ],
      "id": "98e3a4bf"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "chunks_df = pd.read_csv(\"../data/assignment01/chunks.csv\")\n",
        "chunks_df = chunks_df[[\"chunk_id\", \"company\", \"item\", \"chunk_text\"]].dropna().head(200)\n",
        "chunks_df.head()"
      ],
      "id": "c8f91e80",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 2: Build Dense Embeddings"
      ],
      "id": "4868112c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n",
        "embeddings = model.encode(\n",
        "    chunks_df[\"chunk_text\"].tolist(),\n",
        "    batch_size=32,\n",
        "    convert_to_numpy=True,\n",
        "    normalize_embeddings=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "embeddings.shape"
      ],
      "id": "678045a0",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 3: Run Similarity Search"
      ],
      "id": "565eacf9"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "query = \"cybersecurity risk and data privacy concerns\"\n",
        "q_vec = model.encode([query], normalize_embeddings=True)\n",
        "scores = cosine_similarity(q_vec, embeddings)[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "top_idx = np.argsort(scores)[-5:][::-1]\n",
        "neighbor_df = chunks_df.iloc[top_idx].copy()\n",
        "neighbor_df[\"score\"] = scores[top_idx]\n",
        "neighbor_df[[\"chunk_id\", \"company\", \"item\", \"score\"]]"
      ],
      "id": "9a3ea8c7",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 4: Interpret the Neighbors"
      ],
      "id": "e6c2a60b"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "for _, row in neighbor_df.iterrows():\n",
        "    print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
        "    print(row[\"chunk_id\"], row[\"company\"], row[\"item\"], round(row[\"score\"], 3))\n",
        "    print(row[\"chunk_text\"][:500])"
      ],
      "id": "7f6c85d1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## What Students Should Notice\n",
        "\n",
        "- Dense embeddings can retrieve meaningfully related chunks even when wording changes.\n",
        "- SEC text often groups around risk themes like regulation, privacy, litigation, or macroeconomic uncertainty.\n",
        "- Semantic neighbors are useful, but they can also blur distinctions between rival companies if the disclosures are too generic.\n",
        "\n",
